  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Syrian Refugees&#x2019; Justice Concerns and Access to Formal and Informal Justice Systems in Lebanon</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Academics and agencies working on Syrian refugee protection; policy makers</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will provide an improved and broader understanding of the justice needs of Syrian refugee population and the instruments they are using, if any, to access it. Through a research and methodological toolkit, we aim to contribute to a &#x2018;more people-centred approach for Rule of law reform programming in fragile environments&#x2019;. One output is to help researchers and practitioners to design effective solutions in similar situations. The research instrument generated will allow a wide set of stakeholders to gain improved understanding of vulnerable groups&#x2019; concerns and priorities related to access to justice, including how informal justice and formal institutions interact. This will be shared and potentially replicated elsewhere by other practitioner institutions.</narrative>
  </description>
